txtRns.text: OFFICE OF PRIMARY INTEREST:  Program Accounting Services Division.
FILING INSTRUCTION:  The revised tables replace parts of existing tables currently published
in  Bulletin 1767B-2, Work Order Procedure (Electric), dated January 18, 1994.  (See also –
Retirement Unit Conversion Tables for 12.47/7.2 kV (Bulletin 1728F-804)
PURPOSE:  The revised tables concern the applicable retirement units associated with the
construction assembly units included in Bulletin 1728F-804, “Specifications and Drawings for
SUFFIX "G" DENOTES GUIDE DRAWING ONLY. APPLICABLE CONSTRUCTION ASSEMBLIES ARE LISTED SEPARATELY.
INCLUDES 1 CROSSARM ASSEMBLY COMPOSED OF 2 CROSSARMS BOLTED TOGETHER.  IT SHOULD BE TREATED AS HAVING 2 CROSSARMS
UNLESS THE UTILITY TREATS A CROSSARM ASSEMBLY AS A RECORD UNIT SEPARATE FROM INDIVIDUAL CROSSARMS.  IN THAT CASE, THERE
WOULD BE ONLY 1 CROSSARM ASSEMBLY RECORD UNIT.
SINGLE AND CLUSTER-TYPE CAPACITOR HANGERS ARE SEPARATE RECORD UNITS.  NOTE:  RUS BULLETIN 181-2 STIPULATES THAT THIS
RECORD UNIT BE CLASSIFIED IN ACCOUNT 365, OVERHEAD CONDUCTOR AND DEVICES.  CAPACITOR HANGERS ARE BEING RE-CLASSIFIED
TO ACCOUNT 364, POLES, TOWERS & FIXTURES, TO BE MORE CONSISTENT WITH THE CLASSIFICATION OF OF TRANSFORMER CLUSTER
INITIAL RIGHT-OF-WAY CLEARING & WIDENING COSTS ARE TO BE ALLOCATED TO THE RESPECTIVE CONDUCTOR RECORD UNITS
THREE (3) BYPASS ARRESTERS ARE INCLUDED IN THE VOLTAGE REGULATORS BUT ARE NOT CONSIDERED SEPARATE RECORD
UNITS.  THE COSTS OF THESE BYPASS ARRESTERS ARE INCLUDED IN THE VOLTAGE REGULATORS.
ALTHOUGH UNIT M26-5 WAS NOT A CONSTRUCTION ASSEMBLY (MERELY A GUIDE DRAWING) IN THE PREVIOUS SPECIFICATIONS AND
WAS NOT LISTED IN APPENDIX I, EXHIBIT A OF BULLETIN 1767B-2.  IT HAS, HOWEVER, TRADITIONALLY BEEN AFFORDED RECORD UNIT
STATUS AS A SECURITY LIGHT.  NO SUCH CONSTRUCTION UNIT EXISTS IN THE REVISED DRAWINGS AND SPECIFICATIONS.
FOR 3-PHASE TRANSFORMER BANKS, CUTOUTS AND ARRESTERS MOUNTED ADJACENT TO ONE ANOTHER MAY BE REPLACED WITH
A COMBINATION CUTOUT AND ARRESTER.  SPECIFY TYPE USED.
SPECIFY QUANTITY & SIZE OF CAPACITORS AS REQUIRED

notices: Text coordinates are specified with respect to the TrimBox of the page. You will need to adjust if you want raw pdf coordinates.
